<%- include('../../partials/implementer-core.md.ejs', { specificsBlock: `## Svelte / SvelteKit Specifics

### Svelte 5 Runes
- Use \`$state\`, \`$derived\`, \`$effect\`, and \`$props\` runes — never the legacy \`writable\`/\`readable\` store API in new code.
- Keep \`$effect\` bodies free of side effects that alter state — derive values with \`$derived\` instead.
- Type component props explicitly: \`let { title, count = 0 }: { title: string; count?: number } = $props();\`.

### SvelteKit Data Loading
- Use \`+page.server.ts\` load functions for server-side data fetching; return typed objects.
- Validate and parse \`event.params\` and form data with Zod before use in server load functions.
- Use \`+page.ts\` only when data can safely be fetched on the client; prefer server loads for auth-gated routes.

### Testing
- Unit-test server logic by extracting plain functions and exercising them with \`Vitest\` directly — keep \`+page.server.ts\` files thin so the logic under test is framework-free.
- Use \`Vitest\` + \`@testing-library/svelte\` for component tests; mount with \`render(Component, { props })\`.
- Use \`vi.mock\` for SvelteKit module mocks (\`$app/navigation\`, \`$env/static/public\`).
- For E2E and integration coverage, use \`Playwright\` (the SvelteKit-recommended runner) or run \`supertest\` against the deployed adapter when an HTTP entrypoint is available.

### Anti-patterns to avoid
- Never mutate \`$props\` directly — treat props as readonly; lift state up or use a callback.
- Never use \`document\` / \`window\` directly in \`+page.server.ts\` or server load functions.
- Never bypass SvelteKit's \`load\` system with manual \`fetch\` in components for initial data.
- Never use untyped \`any\` in \`PageData\` / \`ActionData\` — define explicit \`Load\` return types.
- Never run database queries inside \`+page.ts\` (client-side load) — only in \`+page.server.ts\`.` }) %>
